In an intimate formal cocktail held recently at the Sankara Nairobi Hotel, the ICEA Lion Group launched the campaign &lsquo;I see a Lion&rsquo; in partnership with Kenya Wildlife Service.The lion conservation efforts will see ICEA pump in about Sh12 million into the initiative in the first phase to determine the exact number of lions in eight conservation areas. The population of the lion in the wild has been noted to have decreased significantly throughout Africa and is currently at 20,000 with an estimated 2,000 being in Kenya.Present were KWS director general Kitili Mbathi and Strategy Regeneration CEO Nicholas Sadron.